==Maps and Areas==
{{Main|Soul Blazer:Maps}}

The game world consists of 32 interconnected maps across 6 acts, with over 170 Soul Lairs to clear.

==Progression==
{{Main|Soul Blazer:Progression}}

The game is divided into 6 Acts:
# '''Grass Valley''' - Underground Castle, Metal Mantis boss
# '''GreenWood''' - Forest shrines, Plantentacle boss
# '''St. Elles''' - Seabed/Ghost Ship, Poseidon boss
# '''Mountain of Souls''' - Nome/Laynole, Stone Guardian boss
# '''Leo's Laboratory''' - Model towns/paintings, Tin Doll boss
# '''Magridd Castle''' - Final dungeons, Deathtoll final boss

Total Soul Lairs: ~120 | Total Bosses: 8

==Characters==
{{Main|Soul Blazer:Characters}}

The Hero is a divine servant sent by The Master to restore 91 souls across 6 acts. Notable characters include:
* '''The Hero''' - Player character with transformation abilities (Mole, Angel, Mouse, Mermaid)
* '''The Master''' - Divine being who guides through shrines
* '''Deathtoll''' - Primary antagonist with 3 battle phases
* '''Dr. Leo''' - Inventor with important story role
* '''Released Souls''' - NPCs freed from monster lairs

==Secrets==
{{Main|Soul Blazer:Secrets}}

Soul Blazer contains numerous hidden elements:
* Hidden treasures and secret rooms
* Glitches: Damage boost skip, GEM overflow, soul dupe, walk through walls
* Easter eggs: Developer credits room, sound test, Quintet references
* Debug mode via Game Genie codes
* Unused content: items, NPCs, music, and maps

==Audio==
{{Main|Soul Blazer:Audio}}

The game's music was composed by Yukihide Takekawa (タケカワユキヒデ). The SNES SPC700 audio driver is located at $07A7F6 in the ROM.

===Soundtrack===
The game features 22 music tracks and 16 sound effects:
* Town themes for each act (Grass Valley, GreenWood, St. Elles, Mountain Village, Leo's Lab, Magridd)
* Dungeon themes (Underground Castle, Forest, Seabed, Ghost Ship, Mountain, Model Town, Painting World, World of Evil)
* Boss Battle and Deathtoll (final boss) themes
* Jingles: Victory, Soul Released, Game Over
* Title Screen, The Shrine, Ending/Credits

